sl7-sensors (1.0.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * sensor-proxy: close the SSC sensor stream across suspend. The ADSP
    keeps pushing indications while the host sleeps and every one is an
    IPCC wakeup — with the stream open, suspend dies within one push
    interval (~250 ms at 4 Hz). Hold a logind delay inhibitor, tear the
    stream down on PrepareForSleep (bypassing the controller guard),
    resubscribe on resume (controller or active claims only).

 -- valeronm <valeriy@hey.com>  Tue, 21 Jul 2026 18:57:34 +0100
sl7-sensors (1.0.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * status: oneshot-aware unit reporting — FAILED with a journalctl
    pointer, "not installed" (LoadState), and "skipped — config not
    extracted (run 'sl7-sensors setup')" when the start condition gated
    the unit, instead of raw systemctl is-active output.
  * Usage goes to stderr on error exits; mode errors carry the
    "sl7-sensors mode: error:" prefix; usage documents setup's
    [windows-root] argument and points at the man page.
  * color stream: clamp channels at 0 — rounding a tiny negative float
    printed "rgb=(3,2,-0)".

 -- valeronm <valeriy@hey.com>  Mon, 20 Jul 2026 23:45:00 +0100

sl7-sensors (1.0.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Test suite: 72 pytest cases — QMI/protobuf framing (with a drift guard
    between read-sensor and sensor-proxy), EMA filter, backlight
    controller math and corrupt-anchor handling, set-mode rewrite, CLI,
    and the setup extraction end-to-end against a fake DriverStore.
    Wired into the package build via dh_auto_test.
  * Systemd sandbox for sl7-sensors.service (ReadWritePaths for the
    DSP-written registry; no PrivateDevices — needs /dev/fastrpc-adsp).
  * Lintian-clean at --fail-on error,warning: sl7-sensors(1) man page,
    libtool build-tree RUNPATH stripped (chrpath), bindnow hardening,
    orphaned GPL-3+ stanza dropped from debian/copyright.
  * Removed the pre-release ssc-sensor-proxy migration from postinst.
  * CI: two-job least-privilege workflow shared with sl7-mac — static
    checks, tag/changelog gate, lintian gate, create-or-update release.
  * Polish: absolute python3 shebangs, prefixed error messages, idle-dim
    caveat and Releases pointer in README.

 -- valeronm <valeriy@hey.com>  Mon, 20 Jul 2026 22:55:00 +0100

sl7-sensors (1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release: SSC sensor bring-up for the Surface Laptop 7 —
    sensors-PD FastRPC file service feeding the DSP registry the sensor
    configuration extracted from the machine's Windows partition,
    net.hadess.SensorProxy daemon with optional direct backlight
    controller, and the unified sl7-sensors CLI (setup, lux, color, mode,
    status).

